Malaysia will give tax breaks on
sales of Islamic bonds for three years from 2012, Prime Minister
Najib Razak said in his budget speech to parliament today.  Income tax deductions for non-ringgit Islamic bonds will be
extended to 2014, he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
